<div id="review_1823690653" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1823690653" />
    <a title="Nathan Rubene dos Santos" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/61969004-nathan-rubene-dos-santos"><img alt="Nathan Rubene dos Santos" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1594064548p2/61969004.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1823690653?book_show_action=true">Sep 15, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nathan Rubene dos Santos" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nathan Rubene dos Santos" href="/user/show/61969004-nathan-rubene-dos-santos">Nathan Rubene dos Santos</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/61969004-nathan-rubene-dos-santos?shelf=travel-literature">travel-literature</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1823690653" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14123553976652739586">From staidly Baghdad, center of compiled scholarly knowledge and Islamic civilization during the Early Middle Ages, to the frontiers of fantasy, the Arab voyagers of the 9th to 13th century took their part in the Herculean effort to make sense of the four corners of the global through empirical, first-hand investigation, though none could overcome the liminal bond between fact and speculative fiction. Geographic &apos;marvels&apos; of antiquity are rehashed and given new twists, such as the biblical story</span>
  <span id="freeText14123553976652739586" style="display:none">From staidly Baghdad, center of compiled scholarly knowledge and Islamic civilization during the Early Middle Ages, to the frontiers of fantasy, the Arab voyagers of the 9th to 13th century took their part in the Herculean effort to make sense of the four corners of the global through empirical, first-hand investigation, though none could overcome the liminal bond between fact and speculative fiction. Geographic 'marvels' of antiquity are rehashed and given new twists, such as the biblical story of Gog and Magog. (Personally, I am now <i>convinced</i> that the Alexandrian Gates are to be found somewhere in the boreal uplands of the Urals, but I digress.) The writing style in translation is clear and sometimes tedious, but it is the wonder of the journey that sticks with you. North is forever foreign to South, West to East.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14123553976652739586" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review1823690653">
  <td colspan="2">
    <div class="updateActionLinks">
