    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_480828957" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/480828957" />
    <a title="Chon Mkliiry" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7154046-chon-mkliiry"><img alt="Chon Mkliiry" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1323554303p2/7154046.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/480828957?book_show_action=true">Dec 19, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Chon Mkliiry" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Chon Mkliiry" href="/user/show/7154046-chon-mkliiry">Chon Mkliiry</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer480828957" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15228981978430361953">Wow! I just finished this. This book is scary, amazing and beautiful. Ibn Fadlan was an Arabic trader during the middle-ages. He is best known for crossing into the land of &quot;Gog and Magog&quot; (if you&apos;re reading the bible) or Yajuj and Majuj (if you&apos;re reading the Koran.) He, of course, didn&apos;t find Gog and Magog. Ibn Fadlan did, however, find many new and novel groups of civilization. He encounters the Ghuzz, Bulghars, the Bhashgirds and the Rus. The Rus were the predecessors to the Vikings. Ibn Fad</span>
  <span id="freeText15228981978430361953" style="display:none">Wow! I just finished this. This book is scary, amazing and beautiful. Ibn Fadlan was an Arabic trader during the middle-ages. He is best known for crossing into the land of "Gog and Magog" (if you're reading the bible) or Yajuj and Majuj (if you're reading the Koran.) He, of course, didn't find Gog and Magog. Ibn Fadlan did, however, find many new and novel groups of civilization. He encounters the Ghuzz, Bulghars, the Bhashgirds and the Rus. The Rus were the predecessors to the Vikings. Ibn Fadlan describes the funeral of one of the Rus' leaders, which is breathtaking, and focuses on many other interesting facets of human civilization of the time such as: theology, diet, clothing,gastronomy and language. <br />The second half of the book explores other Arab travelers to the Russia/ Scandinavia areas after Fadlan. <br />Really quite enjoyable.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15228981978430361953" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


