  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1823620908?book_show_action=true">Dec 05, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ingrid Spera" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ingrid Spera" href="/user/show/20833271-ingrid-spera">Ingrid Spera</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/17617816-ibn-fadlan-and-the-land-of-darkness">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/20833271-ingrid-spera?shelf=getlost2017">getlost2017</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1823620908" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2603659485613442239">I was drawn to read this book after loving the 13th Warrior (movie) and Eaters of the Dead, but it wasn&apos;t what I was expecting/hoping. I don&apos;t mean to say that it&apos;s a bad read, but I was hoping for a fluid tale or biography of this Arab traveler and instead it was a clinical diary that read like an itinerary. While it was interesting and quite short... it was also excessively dry. Maybe if I&apos;d know that going in it wouldn&apos;t have been so bad, but it wasn&apos;t what I was looking for. </span>
  <span id="freeText2603659485613442239" style="display:none">I was drawn to read this book after loving the 13th Warrior (movie) and Eaters of the Dead, but it wasn't what I was expecting/hoping. I don't mean to say that it's a bad read, but I was hoping for a fluid tale or biography of this Arab traveler and instead it was a clinical diary that read like an itinerary. While it was interesting and quite short... it was also excessively dry. Maybe if I'd know that going in it wouldn't have been so bad, but it wasn't what I was looking for. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2603659485613442239" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


